QATAR EXXONMOBILE OPEN
January 3, 2011
Jo-Wilfried Tsonga
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT







J. TSONGA/R. Hidalgo 
  6-2, 6-0 

 THE MODERATOR: Questions, please. 

 Q. It's your first time here. What did it feel like? Does the court feel good and the conditions? Tell us how it feels. 
 JO-WILFRIED TSONGA: Yeah, it felt well. I played a good match. Everybody's friendly with me here. I feel really good. And, no, it's nice.

 Q. Tell us about yourself. You had a lot of injury problems last season. You thought you got over them and it came back. Are you completely fit and free? Tell us about how you feel. 
 JO-WILFRIED TSONGA: Yes, I'm completely fit. Of course it's not really easy to come back after long week without competition, but now I feel good. 
 I'm maybe healthier than before, and, you know, I just enjoy every moment on the court, and that's it. I hope it will continue.

 Q. What do you hope for during this coming year?
 JO-WILFRIED TSONGA: Just play my best tennis ever. That's it.
 You know, I just want improve my tennis, improve my game and stay at the top of the world tennis.

 Q. This time of the year leading into Australia, does that give you a special buzz, a special memory?
 JO-WILFRIED TSONGA: Yeah, of course, because it's one of my favorite tournament. I like play there. I like the atmosphere.
 So of course I want have a good preparation before to be there, and I hope it will be.







END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT